Mons. J'ayreceu a lon temps la vre de 27: cour les depuis un petit

arrivée, sur quoy ie me fin, cenendant il est party auiourchuy
sans ma cognoissance, dont ie suis marq vous preante avoir
patience cinsqu a la semaine prochaine, et delap dence is
doresa vant un menaire a moy non olstant que vous

Kent
London
S my last to you was on the 26 past, to be pleased to be
referted, senc rec yo of 140., exspect olever pr fors bwjff some
other ships becaise off the english soediers that are to come over
or by the ostend contsy, I an told that sayd heliver is a soung
not experted
seaman a god sent him well, I take notice, what you say
mandes
no appearance of goods fallinge, & tnough my last contradictes
in some part the beuijngs of more goods, yett as I told you do as
for yo self, and sot shall bee to ny content, what you shalle
shave geted for mee, either bought or not bought the Rengtted
& all the court shall leave the mooning before the beginging
of the campain & conseguentely I doubt not, butt same newes
coleurs shall come out where in you may not amitt to add
2 a 3 p of the superfines you shall send to me in 1 post or 2
the accompt of bayes & kersies from the nooth which es well
butt I doubt wee omisander stand each other in the insurance
because you ould mil beang here to charge the invoyces with 3
p C. for insurance lett if be, which is that every invoyce be accs
mented with 3 p. P. ano by alors, you discharge my actt of
said parcell, & not as you note for n° 75 because that comes to 3-
, yett for thes tims, I have given you credit so, butt pray for the
futeure charge all the invoyces from the novoh with 3 pc & no
other abatements to be allowed in case of a lost, & so did for merbey
mr. Maynard, & & thinck you do so still with m. Perrebooons, I shall
draw no more on you, biutt iespect some remises when ex. comes above 31 ƒ
& that you pidge itt my intrest, because others write, & will have ex
att 33 a 341: within a month, so in cas you remitt send not above £2 a £
300 attonces, & do as for you self yott wee would thinck that x must,
run up when all things shall be seltted. so that I know not what is best, for
I shall want monney to buy goods. & I doubt Ishall never remitt cheaper
londres Jan du maistre then thent you have ofmee sel dofer Adij 2 februarij A 1696

sedert mijnen van 30 passato den uwen van selven dato becomen
ende over rotterdam weder brieven ie van londen waer bij het schijndt
dat het muntwerck nu voor goet sal voortgaen ende willen sij dat
de wissel seer een maert a parij sal wesen soo dat ick niet wete wat
best gedaen: tis heden hier i dagh en waeren gisteren brieven a 30ƒt
5 a 6 wijnige oft geen gevers, soo ul mij brief niet hebt ingetroecken
soo sent den selven naer londen geindoseert aen de S walter 3 will
kent hebbe wijders wijnich te inlargeren als dat versoecke d'ingeslte
voorts ganck hebben. soude wel willen geassureert sijne d op goderen
mien f in anstoorto golde fry int schip sint joseph capitijn daniel frigeron
vande cangrische eijlanden op rotterdam, geloove hij met het engels
convoije sal afcomen doch onseker, wensche wel te weten waervore
ostij dat te becomen is ben maer ƒ500:- geintresseert a governo
